{"id":385622,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vicky_Cristina_Barcelona","text":"\"Vicky Cristina Barcelona\" is a 2008 Spanish-American romantic comedy-drama movie. It was written and directed by Woody Allen. It is set in the Spanish cities Barcelona and Oviedo. It is about two American women in their twenties who meet an artist, Juan, whilst spending a summer in Spain.\nRebecca Hall playes Vicky, Scarlett Johansson plays Cristina, Javier Bardem plays Juan, Pen\u00E9lope Cruz plays his angry, violent ex-wife Maria. The movie won a Golden Globe Award.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Spain","surface_form":"Spanish","offset":37},{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"American","offset":45},{"uri":"Romance_movie","surface_form":"romantic","offset":54},{"uri":"Comedy-drama","surface_form":"comedy-drama","offset":63},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":76},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"written","offset":90},{"uri":"Movie_director","surface_form":"directed","offset":102},{"uri":"Woody_Allen","surface_form":"Woody Allen","offset":114},{"uri":"Spain","surface_form":"Spanish","offset":144},{"uri":"City","surface_form":"cities","offset":152},{"uri":"Barcelona","surface_form":"Barcelona","offset":159},{"uri":"Oviedo","surface_form":"Oviedo","offset":173},{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":197},{"uri":"Artist","surface_form":"artist","offset":242},{"uri":"Summer","surface_form":"summer","offset":274},{"uri":"Rebecca_Hall","surface_form":"Rebecca Hall","offset":291},{"uri":"Scarlett_Johansson","surface_form":"Scarlett Johansson","offset":318},{"uri":"Javier_Bardem","surface_form":"Javier Bardem","offset":353},{"uri":"Pen%C3%A9lope_Cruz","surface_form":"Pen\u00E9lope Cruz","offset":379},{"uri":"Angry","surface_form":"angry","offset":403},{"uri":"Violent","surface_form":"violent","offset":410},{"uri":"Golden_Globe_Award","surface_form":"Golden Globe Award","offset":449}]}